# Code Reusability

- **Refactor when possible**: If you see repeated code patterns, extract them into reusable components or utilities.
- **Reuse existing components**: Before creating new components, check if similar functionality already exists in `app/components/`.
- **Follow DRY principle**: Don't Repeat Yourself. Consolidate duplicate logic.
- **Check styleguide components**: Components in `app/components/styleguide/` are designed to be reusable across the project.

## Reusable UI Components

Located in `app/components/ui/`:

- **Button** (`app/components/ui/Button.tsx`) - Button/link component with variants (`primary`, `primary-2`, `secondary`, `secondary-2`, `outline`, `ghost`) and sizes (`sm`, `md`, `lg`)
- **Card** (`app/components/ui/Card.tsx`) - Card container with border and background styling, padding options (`none`, `sm`, `md`, `lg`)
- **SectionHeading** (`app/components/ui/SectionHeading.tsx`) - Section header with title, optional subtitle, and centered option

